text.tspan: Far away in the castle on the cliffside
Past the man made of sticks and reeds
Through old letters in the abandoned laboratory
Following the fleet quill of the undertaker
TIPTOEING over piles of TWIG Dolls
And over the swampy fog Covered Bridge
The Doctor will see you now
Then you have a date with the chainsaw Man
The worms always have the leftovers
The crows Frenzy and fight over the smaller pieces
The oaks GROW taller and creek in the wind
The witch rides high overhead in front of the moon
Good thing you left a message telling where you were headed
The vampire forgot to feed his children of the night
The ghost is in the hallway mirror
The assylum gates yawn wide for new guests
There are crocadiles in the moat, you know
Grandmother Nightshade always said there were
But as the coffin creeks and echoes in the toomb
And Blood Seeps through the cracks
And dark pendulous clouds close in
It is aparent you probably should have just stayed home today.
Along the Balcony OVERlooking the beast
